<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><legaldoc><law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection chaptername="Schools" statutenumber="79-1231"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><statuteno>79-1231</statuteno><catchline>Special education; payment; to whom.</catchline><para>When special education is provided by an educational service unit for children with disabilities as defined in section 79-1118.01, the payments provided by sections 79-1126 to 79-1144 shall be made to such educational service unit.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1967, c. 517, &#167; 1, p. 1737; </para><para>Laws 1986, LB 1177, &#167; 38; </para><para>Laws 1987, LB 367, &#167; 72; </para><para>R.S.1943, (1994), &#167; 79-2213; </para><para>Laws 1996, LB 900, &#167; 948; </para><para>Laws 1997, LB 346, &#167; 58. </para></source></law></legaldoc>